before.description:
Add labelPolicies config for per-label retention rules.

## Schema Change (config.schema.json)
```json
{
  "archive": {
    "labelPolicies": {
      "type": "object",
      "additionalProperties": {
        "oneOf": [
          { "const": "never" },
          { "type": "object", "properties": { "daysUntilArchive": { "type": "integer" } } }
        ]
      },
      "default": {},
      "description": "Per-label retention policies",
      "examples": [{
        "epic-type": "never",
        "bug": { "daysUntilArchive": 3 },
        "documentation": { "daysUntilArchive": 14 }
      }]
    }
  }
}
```

## Implementation
1. Update config.schema.json with labelPolicies
2. Archive evaluates policies per-task
3. Most restrictive policy wins (never > longer days > default)
4. Add --show-policies flag to display effective policies

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Schema supports labelPolicies object
- [ ] 'never' policy prevents archiving
- [ ] Custom daysUntilArchive per label
- [ ] Multiple labels use most restrictive

